main event: A bright, star-like object was observed in the sky over a remote location in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was observed for over 4 hours, from 1635Z to 2055Z.
The object was first sighted at a bearing of 252 degrees and an altitude of 70 degrees, and then disappeared over the horizon at a bearing of 220 degrees.
The object was described as being as bright as a 1st magnitude star.
The report was filed in accordance with JANAP 146D protocols for reporting unidentified aerial phenomena.
The report was forwarded to various military and intelligence entities for further analysis.
